        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1962-06-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1962-06-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="136"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d136">
                <head>136. Memorandum of Conversation<note n="0" type="source" xml:id="d136fn0"
                        >Source: Kennedy Library, National Security Files, Countries Series, India,
                        General, 6/11/62-6/16/62. Secret. Drafted on June 15 by <persName
                            corresp="#p_KRW1">Komer</persName>. According to the President’s
                        Appointment Book, the meeting was held at the White House. (Ibid.)</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            type="conversation-or-meeting-date" when="1962-06-14">June 14,
                            1962</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="participants">
                    <head>PRESENT</head>
                    <item>The President</item>
                    <item>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_BGW1">George Ball</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_JUA1">U. Alexis Johnson</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_GJK1">Galbraith</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_MCWP1">McConaughy</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_GJP1">James P. Grant</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_MNRS1">Robert McNamara</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_BMG1">McG. Bundy</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_BWP1">William P. Bundy</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_KRW1">R.W. Komer</persName>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <p rend="center">DECISIONS TAKEN AT PRESIDENT’S MEETING ONCOUNTERING <gloss
                        target="#t_MIG1">MIG</gloss> SALE TO INDIA, 14 JUNE 1962</p>
                <p>The President was opposed to subsidizing the sale of two Lightning Mark II
                    squadrons to India for rupees, at a likely cost of around $60 million.</p>
                <p>Instead he approved telling Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_MH1"
                        >Macmillan</persName> that we would be willing to share 50/50 the hard
                    currency cost of one Lightning squadron. We would also finance 75 per cent of
                    the further development cost of the Orpheus engine, if the Indians accepted the
                        <gloss target="#t_UK1">UK</gloss> offer. To complete the package, he
                    approved a simultaneous US offer to sell India nine C-130 transports for rupees.
                    All of the above are contingent upon the Indians not buying the <gloss
                        target="#t_MIG1">MIG</gloss>-21.</p>
                <p>The President directed that Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_GJK1"
                        >Galbraith</persName> make a strong presentation to
                        <persName>Nehru</persName> on the likely blow to US aid prospects if the
                    Indians bought <gloss target="#t_MIG1">MIG</gloss>s. He agreed to send a
                    personal letter to <persName>Nehru</persName> for <persName corresp="#p_GJK1"
                        >Galbraith</persName> to present after his first talk with
                        <persName>Nehru</persName>.</p>
                <p>The President desired that we tell <persName corresp="#p_AKM1">Ayub</persName>
                    frankly why we were trying to forestall an Indian purchase of <gloss
                        target="#t_MIG1">MIG</gloss>s. He expressed willingness to write <persName
                        corresp="#p_AKM1">Ayub</persName> a personal letter to try to disarm him. He
                    reserved judgment on the suggestion that we attempt to placate <persName
                        corresp="#p_AKM1">Ayub</persName> by offering him the public security
                    reassurances he has been seeking.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="strong">RWK</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
